The '''Berlin State Ballet''' (German '''Staatsballett Berlin''') is the principal [[ballet]] company in the German capital of [[Berlin]]. It was created in 2004 through a merger of the separate ballet companies of the city's three opera houses at a time when the city was going through a financial crisis. It is one of the largest ballet companies in Western Europe with approximately 90 dancers.
Since 2004, the Berlin State Ballet, alongside the [[Berlin State Opera]], the [[Deutsche Oper Berlin]], the [[Komische Oper Berlin]] comprise the {{Interlanguage link multi|Stiftung Oper in Berlin|de|3=Stiftung Oper in Berlin|lt=Berlin Opera Foundation}}.<ref>[http://www.oper-in-berlin.de/en_EN/news/index/ Oper in Berlin]</ref> The Berlin State Ballet inaugural general and artistic director, dancer and choreographer [[Vladimir Malakhov (dancer)|Vladimir Malakhov]], was a director of the ballet of the [[Berlin State Opera|Berlin Opera]] before the companies merged to form the Berlin State Ballet.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.pointemagazine.com/call-board-2412800126.html|title=Call Board|date=2001-11-30|work=Pointe|access-date=2017-07-27|language=en}}</ref> He led the company for ten years, creating a mixed repertoire of classical titles and contemporary choreography. A star dancer himself, Malakhov was not only managing, but also performing with the company.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.staatsballett-berlin.de/de/ensemble/vladimir-malakhov/114|title=Vladimir Malakhov|website=www.staatsballett-berlin.de|access-date=2017-07-27}}</ref>
In 2014, [[Nacho Duato]] became general and artistic director at the Berlin State Ballet with an initial five years term. He created new choreography for the company, and oversaw restagings of some of his signature ballets, created in [[Madrid]], [[Saint Petersburg|St. Petersburg]] and [[Munich]], in Berlin. In 2016, [[Michael Müller (politician)|Michael Mueller]], [[Governing Mayor of Berlin|Mayor of Berlin]], announced that the city will not extend Duato's contract with the company when it expires in 2019. [[Sasha Waltz]] and [[Johannes Ohman]] are to succeed him as joint artistic directors of the Berlin State Ballet.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/09/10/arts/dance/staatsballett-berlin-sasha-waltz-johannes-ohman-to-succeed-nacho-duato.html|title=2 New Faces for Staatsballett Berlin, When Nacho Duato Leaves in 2019|last=Sulcas|first=Roslyn|date=2016-09-09|work=The New York Times|access-date=2017-07-25|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref>
