{{Nihongo|'''Hayashiya Kikuō'''|林家 木久扇|Hayashiya Kikuō|born October 19, 1937|lead=yes}} is a Japanese [[rakugo]] performer and a featured member of the long-running television comedy show ''[[Shōten]]''. His real name is {{Nihongo|'''Toyota Hiroshi'''|豊田 洋}}, although he is most widely known by his previous comedian name {{Nihongo|Hayashiya Kikuzō|林家 木久蔵}}, a name he was the first to assume. The new Hayashiya Kikuzō is his son, the former Hayashiya Kikuo.<ref name="HuffPost">{{cite web|title=「人一倍生きなくちゃ」3度の大病を乗り越えた林家木久扇・木久蔵親子の噺|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.jp/2016/07/27/hayashiyaoyako_n_11174054.html|website=ハフィントンポスト|accessdate=16 February 2017}}</ref> On ''Shōten'', he always wears a yellow [[kimono]]. He is known for making commonplace jokes and usually "plays the fool." He is a mood maker.

== Kikuzō Ramen ==
Kikuō has a chain of noodle shops named after him called "Kikuzō Ramen." On ''Shōten'', he often advertises Kikuzō Ramen, but other members joke about it being very flavorless.

